parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty gear selector can cause the vehicle to roll even when in park, leading to accidents or injuries. The error message "Secure Vehicle Against Rolling" can be distracting and may cause the driver to lose focus on the road.
symptoms: Error message "Secure Vehicle Against Rolling" appears on the dashboard
gear selector fails to engage properly
vehicle rolls even when in park.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty sunroof shade can obstruct the driver's view, leading to accidents or injuries. The sudden failure of the sunroof shade can also cause distraction and startle the driver.
symptoms: Sunroof shade becomes detached from the retractable component
sunroof shade sags or blocks the view of the rearview mirror
sunroof shade falls on the driver or passengers.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the gear selector spring can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to a warning message "Secure Vehicle Against Rolling" or "Secure Vehicle with Parking Brake when stopped." This can cause confusion and potentially lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The warning message "Secure Vehicle Against Rolling" or "Secure Vehicle with Parking Brake when stopped" appears on the dashboard
the vehicle rolls or moves unexpectedly
the parking brake is not engaged despite being activated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission malfunction can cause the vehicle to hesitate or delay acceleration, leading to potential accidents or injuries.
symptoms: there is a delay in response to the accelerator pedal
the vehicle drifts or moves unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the panoramic sunroof shade can cause a dangerous obstruction to visibility, leading to potential accidents or hazards while driving.
symptoms: The sunshade partially or completely detaches from the ceiling of the vehicle
causing a sagging or hanging obstruction to visibility
